Description
============
- Dynamically change color of fill-column-indicator (fci) to indicate the fraction of `fill-column' occupied by the current line.
- Color is cyan if current line is completely empty and red when completely filled.
- This can be inverted (customize).
- Optionally (customize), determine color based on cursor position, irrespective of length of line.
- Calculate color every time Emacs is idle for `color-fci-call-freq-sec' (customize).

Minor Mode
===========
Enable `color-fci-mode' and `display-fill-column-indicator-mode'.

Customization group
====================
Customize using group `color-fci'.
